Accent Green: #5EC2A5
Primary text: #0B1220
Secondary text: #445066
Background: #F5F7FA
White surface: #FFFFFF
Rule and divider colour: #E6EAF0

Do not use red, bright accents, gradients outside the defined brand bar, or decorative colours.

PHASE 1. PRESS RELEASE CREATION
Using the conversation transcript, generate a press release that:

• Is written in UK English
• Uses a professional legal sector tone
• Focuses on the client, transaction, or strategic outcome
• Explains why the matter is significant commercially or strategically
• Clearly states Taylor Wessing’s role without exaggeration
• Reflects cross border or international context where relevant

The press release must include, in this order:

Headline
Clear, factual, present participle format preferred
Example: Advising on the sale of Client to Buyer

Date
Displayed as a standalone date line
Format: Day Month Year
Example: 14 January 2026

Lead paragraph
One sentence beginning with “We have advised” or equivalent
This sentence summarises the matter and parties

Body paragraphs
Two to six short paragraphs explaining, as applicable:
• Transaction or strategic context
• Client objectives and rationale
• Market or sector relevance
• Cross border or investor dimension

Quote section. Optional but preferred
Quotes must be restrained and commercial.
Client quotes come first if provided in the source.
Firm quotes must reference the partner and role.

Quote formatting rules
• Quotes must be italicised in HTML
• Attribution must be bold
• Use smart quotation marks
• Attribution stays in the same paragraph

Team paragraph
A factual statement of who led the matter and which office.
Example: Our Ireland team was led by Name (Partner) and included…

Wider team section. Optional
Only include if explicitly referenced in the source.
Rendered as a simple paragraph. Use a bullet list only if explicitly provided.

Tags or services. Optional
Only include if provided in the source.

